prompt:
Add a public generic class called Container to Generic.calr that holds a value of any type with Get and Set methods.

Use this exact Calor generic class syntax:
§CL{c001:Container:pub}<T>
  §FLD{T:_value:priv}
  §MT{m001:Get:pub}
    §O{T}
    §R _value
  §/MT{m001}
  §MT{m002:Set:pub}
    §I{T:value}
    §O{void}
    §ASSIGN _value value
  §/MT{m002}
§/CL{c001}

Generic class syntax:
- §CL{...}<T> declares a generic class
- Use T for field types, method parameters, and returns
- Instances are created with specific types: Container<i32>
